<s> You are the one who deals with agencies/bureaucracies/standardisers.  </s>
<s> To me it's "implicit" in the second dictionary sense as "unquestioned" more than in the first sense of "implied".  </s>
<s> I would recommend that if it is to become "explicit" that it be addressed in some way in the foreword so that it is emphasized that we aren't draconian, but politic in our willingness to understand acceptable compromise, etc.  </s>
<s> If it is boringly included in every (almost every?) checkpoint it might look a bit ridiculous?  </s>
<s> Len always spoke of the need to understand a designer's purpose in making certain decisions and this is part of what "within reason" is intended to accomplish.  </s>
<s> In other words we are proceeding with the understanding that whoever is consulting these guidelines has the same goals we do: to make stuff accessible to PWD - and by inclusion, to everyone.  </s>
